deepDive.body:
SSE format: HTTP response with Content-Type: text/event-stream. Each event is: data: {json_payload}

. For LLM streaming: each event carries a delta (the new tokens generated since the last event). Final event: data: [DONE]

 (OpenAI) or an event with stop_reason (Anthropic). Client implementation: EventSource API (browser) or requests + iter_lines() (Python). Important: set the response headers correctly: Content-Type: text/event-stream, Cache-Control: no-cache, X-Accel-Buffering: no (disables Nginx/proxy buffering that would delay events). Intermediate proxies (load balancers, API gateways) must support SSE — some buffer responses by default; configure stream pass-through. [1]
